/**
 * ChronosService — one client for both of Chronos-Mind's read surfaces.
 *
 * REST (memory management): catchers (memory banks), the recall tester and
 * trace listing — mirrors the daemon's own frontend client.
 *
 * GraphQL `/graphql` (read-only backtracking): conversations → messages →
 * steps, tasks, session-scoped traces. One `gql()` POST helper plus a typed
 * method per query; each asks for exactly the fields the UI renders. To
 * expand, add a method with its own query string — the backend needs no
 * changes until a whole new root field is required. All GraphQL root fields
 * are offset-paged (`skip`/`take` → `{ items, totalCount }`).
 *
 * baseUrl is empty for same-origin, or a prefix like '/api/chronos' that a
 * dev proxy rewrites to http://localhost:53301.
 */
